Secretary of Veterans Affairs Dennis McDonough, Senior Advisor to the President Cedric Richmond, and Deputy Homeland Security Advisor Josh Geltzer hosted a virtual meeting with over 70 veteran, military family, caregiver, and survivor organizations. The meeting focused on the ongoing drawdown of U.S. forces in Afghanistan. The officials expressed condolences for the recent terrorist attacks in Kabul and discussed how the organizations can support the drawdown. Key priorities highlighted by the organizations included providing mental health and support services for veterans and military families, ensuring adequate funding for resettlement agencies, and combating extremist rhetoric and misinformation about Afghan allies being resettled in U.S. communities. The administration officials reiterated the President's commitment to both allies and service members, expressed continued engagement and partnership with the groups, and thanked participants for their efforts to help veterans, military families, and Afghan allies.